channel.title: Compiler Errors [PI]
channel.description:
I have run into to some errors, when downloading a server, I have tried to fix them myself however it isn't going very well. I was hoping you guys could give me a hand, or explain what's going wrong here?
[IMG]http://i60.tinypic.com/2mplcfo.png[/img]
If you even explain what brings about the error In one I should be able to understand the rest. Thanks guys, get back to me asap:P

item.title: Compiler Errors [PI]
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Well a few things could cause this…

  1. You didn’t import the MeleeData class. (IDEs would alert you of this…)
  2. You imported it, but you forgot to change the compiler code to read the directory it’s in. (This is why we love IDEs, it does this part for you.)
  3. It doesn’t exist, due to spelling error or etc. (IDEs can also notice a spelling error, sometimes but not always)

Soo. Yea. A great solution, as I’ve told you plenty of times in the past, is to get an IDE
